Guiness Beef Stew
  --Cook's Country

3 1/2-4 lb boneless beef chuck eye roast, pulled apart at seams, trimmed, and cut into 1 1/2" pieces
salt and pepper
3 tbsp vegetable oil
2 onions, chopped fine
1 tbsp tomato paste
2 garlic cloves, minced
1/4 c ap flour
3 c low sodium chicken broth
1 1/4 c guiness
1 1/2 tbsp packed dark brown sugar
1 tsp minced fresh thyme
1 1/2 lbs yukon gold potatoes, unpeeled, cut into 1" pieces
1 lb carrots, peeled and cut into 1" pieces
2 tbsp minced fresh parsley

Adjust oven rack to lower middle position and heat oven to 325F. Season beef with salt and pepper. Heat oil in dutch oven over medium high heat until shimmering. Add onions and 1/4 tsp salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until well browned, 8-10 min. Add tomato paste and garlic and cook until rust colored and fragrant, ~2 min. Stir in flour and cook for 1 min. Whisk in broth, 3/4 c guiness, sugar, and thyme, scraping up any browned bits. Bring to simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~3 min. Stir in beef and return to simmer. Transfer to oven and cook, uncovered, for 90 min, stirring halfway through cooking. Stir in potatoes and carrots and continue cooking until beef and vegetables are tender, ~1 hr, stirring halfway through cooking. Stir in remaining guiness and parsley. Season with salt and pepper to taste, and serve.
